oracle.apps.fnd.applcore.globalSearch.ui.tile
Interface TilePart

All Known Implementing Classes:
CategorySearchFilterItem, DateRangeSearchFilterItem, FacetSearchFilterItem, KeywordSearchFilterItem, SearchableObjectSearchFilterItem, SearchFilterItem, SingleSelectionSearchFilterItem, TagSearchFilterItem
public interface TilePart

An interface for defining a Tile Part. There may be many Tile Parts in a Tile, they are held in an order important to the Tile.

Since:
11.1.1.7.2

getLOVId

java.lang.String getLOVId()
Get the List of Values Id (component Id) of the component that will act as a LOV for this Tile Part. TileMethods.tilePartSelection(ActionEvent) will use this to determine the popup to show LOV items in.

Returns:
LOV ID, for example "gssrclov" is the Category Search Filter Item LOV.

isFilterable

boolean isFilterable()
Is this Tile Part Filterable? Controls whether a click on it will trigger a tilePartSelection.

Returns:
true if filterable, false otherwise.
See Also:
TileMethods

isRendered

boolean isRendered()
Is this tile part rendered?

Returns:
true if rendered, false otherwise.

isInlineSelection

boolean isInlineSelection()
Does this tile part support inline selection. If so a picker will be displayed in the tile itself instead of a LOV used.

Returns:
true if inline selector, false otherwise.

getInlineSelectionType

java.lang.String getInlineSelectionType()
If isInlineSelection() == true, what type of selection is required?

Current types are "multiple" and "single" for selecting String types.

Returns:
"multiple" or "single".

getInlineSelectionModel

java.lang.Object getInlineSelectionModel()
Get the data model for inline selections.

Returns:
Object representing the model that will be bound to the UI.
